Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_self_heat_analysis_mode(25.10)          set_self_heat_analysis_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_self_heat_analysis_mode  -  Specifies  the  number of tiles, layer-
       based <alpha> coefficients, <beta> coefficients, and list of cells with
       cell thermal resistances

Syntax
       set_self_heat_analysis_mode

       [-help]

       [-alpha_parameters {{<layer_name> < <alpha>overlapping > <  <alpha>con-
       necting >}+}]

       [-beta_parameters {C1 C2 C3}]

       [-cell_thermal_resistance_file <filename]>

       [-detail_delta_temperature_file <filename]>

       [-detail_delta_temperature_region {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}]

       [-die_instance_input_signal_em <filename>]

       [-die_instance_name <dieinstname>]

       [-instance_delta_temperature_file <filename>]

       [-instance_power_file <filename>]

       [-report_conn_pin_wire <filename>]

       [-scale_rms_limit <value>]

       [-tile_delta_temperature_file <filename>]

       [-tiles {<n_tile_in_x> <m_tile_in_y>}]

       Specifies the number of tiles, layer-based <alpha> coefficients, <beta>
       coefficients,  and  list  of  cells with cell thermal resistances. This
       command will use the static power data to compute delta T FEOL for  all
       instances in the design. This command:

              * computes the RMS currents on signal wires

              * computes the RMS currents on power network wires

              * generates  Detail Delta Temperature File (ddt), Instance Delta
                Temperature File (idt), and Tile Delta Temperature File (tdt)

       The command supports both single-die and multi-die flows.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each set_self_heat_analysis_mode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man set_self_heat_analysis_mode.

       -alpha_parameters {{<layer_name> < <alpha>overlapping > < <alpha>con-
       necting >}+}
              Specifies  the  alpha parameters for all layers. It is the metal
              layer effect.

       -beta_parameters {C1 C2 C3}
              Specifies the thermal coupling effect coefficient Value.

       -cell_thermal_resistance_file <filename>
              Specifies the name of the cell's equivalent  thermal  resistance
              file.  The  specified  file contains the list of cells and their
              corresponding thermal resistance value. The unit of thermal  re-
              sistance  is  in  <degree>C/W (temperature rise per unit rate of
              heat dissipation).

              The format of the file is:

              <cell_name> <thermal_resistance_in_C/W>

              To get instance deltaT, use half of the  instance  power  multi-
              plied by the cell thermal resistance.

       -detail_delta_temperature_file <filename>
              Specifies the name of the generated BEOL detailed delta-tempera-
              ture file.

       -detail_delta_temperature_region {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies  the  region coordinates for generating detailed delta
              temperature file.

       -die_instance_input_signal_em <filename>
              Specifies the setup Tcl script for each die instance.

       -die_instance_name <dieinstname>
              Specifies the die instance name for multi-die analysis. This op-
              tion is only available in  multi-die  analysis  (set_rail_analy-
              sis_mode -die_mode multi-die).

       -instance_delta_temperature_file <filename>
              Specifies  the  name of the generated FEOL instance-based delta-
              temperature file.

       -instance_power_file <filename>
              Specifies a file for instances and  their  corresponding  static
              power.  It is a two column format of <<instance_name>> and <<to-
              tal_power>>.

       -report_conn_pin_wire <filename>
              Reports results on wires connecting to cell pins.

       -scale_rms_limit <value>
              Specifies the scale factor for the root-mean-square (rms)  limit
              relaxation  factor  during Electromigration current limit analy-
              sis.

       -tile_delta_temperature_file <filename>
              Specifies the name of the generated FEOL/BEOL tile-based  delta-
              temperature file.

       -tiles <{n_tile_in_x m_tile_in_y}>
              Specifies  the  number of tiles in the x and y directions in the
              tile-based delta temperature file.

Examples
              * The following command is an  example  of  set_self_heat_analy-
                sis_mode command:

                set_self_heat_analysis_mode \

                -die_instance_name die0 \

                -alpha_parameters  {{M1  0.74  0.85}  {M2  0.62 0.85} {M3 0.53
                0.85} {M4 0.42 0.85} {M5 0.32 0.85} {M6 0.26  0.85}  {M7  0.26
                0.85}  {M8 0.26 0.85} {M9 0.26 0.85} {M10 0.26 0.85} {M11 0.26
                0.85} {M12 0.26 0.85}} \

                -beta_parameters {0.00423 -0.00045 0.81534}\

                -instance_power_file ./dynamic_power.rpt \

                -cell_thermal_resistance_file TRF.txt \

                -instance_delta_temperature_file sh_itm.txt \

                -tile_delta_temperature_file sh_ttm.txt \

                -tiles {10 10} \

                -detail_delta_temperature_file power_detail_die0.rpt

                set_self_heat_analysis_mode \

                -die_instance_name die1 \

                -alpha_parameters {{M1 0.74 0.85}  {M2  0.62  0.85}  {M3  0.53
                0.85}  {M4  0.42  0.85} {M5 0.32 0.85} {M6 0.26 0.85} {M7 0.26
                0.85} {M8 0.26 0.85} {M9 0.26 0.85} {M10 0.26 0.85} {M11  0.26
                0.85} {M12 0.26 0.85}} \

                -beta_parameters {0.00423 -0.00045 0.81534}\

                -instance_power_file ./dynamic_power.rpt \

                -cell_thermal_resistance_file TRF.txt \

                -instance_delta_temperature_file sh_itm.txt \

                -tile_delta_temperature_file sh_ttm.txt \

                -tiles {10 10} \

                -detail_delta_temperature_file power_detail_die1.rpt

                set_self_heat_analysis_mode \

                -die_instance_name die2 \

                -alpha_parameters  {{M1  0.74  0.85}  {M2  0.62 0.85} {M3 0.53
                0.85} {M4 0.42 0.85} {M5 0.32 0.85} {M6 0.26  0.85}  {M7  0.26
                0.85}  {M8 0.26 0.85} {M9 0.26 0.85} {M10 0.26 0.85} {M11 0.26
                0.85} {M12 0.26 0.85}} \

                -beta_parameters {0.00423 -0.00045 0.81534}\

                -instance_power_file ./dynamic_power.rpt \

                -cell_thermal_resistance_file TRF.txt \

                -instance_delta_temperature_file sh_itm.txt \

                -tile_delta_temperature_file sh_ttm.txt \

                -tiles {10 10} \

                -detail_delta_temperature_file power_detail_die2.rpt

